README for mesa


OVERLAY NOTES

This overlay deviates from the upstream CRUX `mesa` port. The stock Pkgfile
builds a wide set of Gallium3D and Vulkan drivers (nouveau, r300, r600,
radeonsi, svga, virgl, i915, plus optional d3d12/crocus/iris/zink/vulkan
backends), auto-detected based on which optional dependencies happen to be
installed.

None of that applies here. This board (an ARM11/ARMv6 SoC, iMAPx200) has no
dedicated GPU of any kind - no Adreno, Mali, VideoCore, Radeon, Intel, or
Nvidia hardware - so every one of those drivers would be dead code, never
loaded at runtime. Worse, building the `freedreno` Gallium driver (part of
the upstream `auto` selection) triggers a GCC 7.5.0 internal compiler error
("sorry, unimplemented: non-trivial designated initializers not supported")
in `src/freedreno/fdl/fd6_view.cc` - a real GCC limitation, not a bug in
Mesa's code, and not worth chasing for a driver this system will never use.

This Pkgfile instead builds only `-Dgallium-drivers=llvmpipe` (CPU
rasterization via LLVM JIT) with Vulkan and all vendor-specific
drivers/layers disabled.


All the `prt-get isinst ...`-driven conditional logic for optional hardware
support (VA-API, lm_sensors, libunwind, Wayland, Vulkan drivers/layers,
rusticl, d3d12) was removed for the same reason: none of it is reachable
on hardware with no GPU and no plan to add Wayland.
